cloud.jgo.jjdom

Class JjDom

  • java.lang.Object
    • cloud.jgo.jjdom.JjDom
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    jQuerySupport, java.io.Serializable

    public final class JjDom
extends java.lang.Object
implements jQuerySupport, java.io.Serializable
    Version:
    1.0.2

    jGo.cloud/JjDom


    Description :
    This technology basically allows you to create or work on a single html document.
    Moreover you have the possibility to work with jquery and css,
    to migrate the site and update it. You can see your site dynamically
    , at any moment, both the code and the page (front end). JjDom is
    a union between java, jquery and javascript, and the dom structure.
    here are the simple steps to follow to use jjdom :

    1. You create a document - newDocument() | newDocument(String)
    2. You configure jquery by calling the method jqueryInit()
    3. You add the main tags to the web page
    4. Call the printDocumentMarkup() method to show the current html markup
    5. Let's move on to selection with the method $(String) or jquery(String)
    6. Call some jQuery method
    7. See the page preview by calling the method preview()


    Here is the url for general documentation :
    https://www.jgo.cloud/jjdom


    Jjdom
    (Write a little and get a lot)
    J - Java
    j - jQuery
    Dom - Dom

    1 Example - we hide and show all the paragraphs belonging to the element with id "container":
    $("#container p").hide("slow").show("slow");

    2 Example - animates the opacity of all the paragraphs and then applies a "slide" effect of closing and opening on them:
    $("p").fadeOut("slow").fadeIn("slow").slideUp(3000).slideDown(3000);

    3 Example - at the click of the element with id "#button" we hide or show all the paragraphs:
    $("#button").on("click",new jQueryfunction() {
    @Override
    public void function(Event event) {
    jquery("p").toggle("slow");
      }
    });

    4 Example - at the click of the element with id "#button" we hide or show all the paragraphs:
    $("p.internal").css("background","red");

    Martire91
